key_points: Internet sleuths claim Brian Laundrie was seen reading Jeff VanderMeer’s “Annihilation,” a novel about missing women, in a video on the couple’s YouTube channel.
“Annihilation” is about four women who enter a mysterious area where three disappear and one stays behind.
TikTok user Alyssa Rose called the video “disturbing” and suggested it should be investigated by the police.
Some TikTok users believe the connection between the book and Gabby Petito's case is far-fetched.
The video was uploaded to the “Nomadik Statik” channel on August 19.
A 2018 movie based on the novel starred Natalie Portman and Jennifer Jason Leigh.
The FBI has likely found Gabby Petito's body in a Wyoming national park.
The discovery of the body was deemed “heartbreaking” by Laundrie family's attorney.
Teton County Coroner Dr. Brent Blue confirmed the discovery of a body at Bridger-Teton National Forest.
Petito went missing last month during a trip with Laundrie, who returned home without her and then disappeared.
